*log*

(PHP 4, PHP 5, PHP 7, PHP 8)

log â€” Natural logarithm

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  log(float $num, float $base = M_E): float~

If the optional {base} parameter is specified, log() returns log[base] {num},
otherwise log() returns the natural logarithm of {num}.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{num}

  The value to calculate the logarithm for

{base}

  The optional logarithmic base to use (defaults to 'e' and so to the natural
  logarithm).

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

The logarithm of {num} to {base}, if given, or the natural logarithm.

===============================================================================
[ See Also ]

 * |log10| - Base-10 logarithm
 * |exp| - Calculates the exponent of e
 * |pow| - Exponential expression
 * |error_log| - Send an error message to the defined error handling routines


